I mean.translation[0].definitions[0].def: used when explaining or giving an example of something, or when pausing to think about what you are going to say next
I mean.translation[0].definitions[0].exa: You’re more of an expert than me. I mean, you’ve got all that experience.
It’s just not right. I mean, it’s unfair isn’t it?
I mean.translation[0].definitions[1].def: used to quickly correct something you have just said
I mean.translation[0].definitions[1].exa: She plays the violin, I mean the viola, really well.
